Minimum Characters to Add for Palindrome
ğŸ“Œ Problem Statement

Given a string s, find the minimum number of characters to add at the front of the string to make it a palindrome.

A palindrome is a string that reads the same forward and backward.

ğŸ§  Approach

Instead of checking every prefix (which would take O(nÂ²) time), we use an optimized KMP (Knuthâ€“Morrisâ€“Pratt) based approach to solve the problem in O(n) time.

ğŸ” Key Idea

Reverse the string.

Create a new string:

temp = s + "#" + reverse(s)


Compute the LPS (Longest Prefix Suffix) array for temp.

The last value of the LPS array gives the length of the longest palindromic prefix.

Final Answer:

len(s) - lps[-1]

ğŸš€ Time & Space Complexity
Complexity	Value
Time	O(n)
Space	O(n)
